article.headline: Cent. Michigan 88, Buffalo 82
article.story: MOUNT PLEASANT, Mich. -- Jordan Bitzer had 22 points and eight rebounds to lead Central Michigan to an 88-82 victory against Buffalo on Thursday night. Robbie Harman added 19 points and Marko Spica 12 for the Chippewas (11-9, 6-2 Mid-American), who stayed in first place in the MAC's West Division, a half-game in front of Ball State, which defeated Bowling Green on Thursday. Rodney Pierce scored 22 points and Calvin Betts 15 for Buffalo (11-9, 4-5). Jalin Thomas had 11 points for Central Michigan, which shot 56.7 percent (17 of 30) in the second half.
